117. 
<taxonomicName id="D8BA8C250F2E4DD04E7B1FB0D9FAE17E" LSID="AC489E78-3E5A-50A0-8128-52B811543A1A" authority="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke 1882: 519)." authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hildebrandtii" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">Convolvulus hildebrandtii Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke 1882: 519).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A3E0A8E551DAF9D31912E0D72E1C645A" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="2FC8C74C964E69E03A3F980F7C425976" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName id="6BD657A595B6F6F5507CCA5C0E714FC6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus filipes" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filipes">Convolvulus filipes</taxonomicName>
Balf.f., Proc. Roy. Soc. Edinburgh 12: 82. 1884. (
<bibRefCitation id="931C62749DD372124C72D4D30744741B" author="Balfour, IB" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Society of Edinburgh" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" pagination="76 - 98" refId="B21" refString="Balfour, IB, 1884. Diagnoses Plantarum Novarum, part 3. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Edinburgh 12: 76 - 98" title="Diagnoses Plantarum Novarum, part 3." volume="12" year="1884">Balfour 1884</bibRefCitation>
: 82). Type. SOCOTRA, 
<emphasis id="32D47C38E2455CE540478627968F279A" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Balfour et al.</emphasis>
238 (lectotype K!, designated here).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9D01F3CDA4968A5F7FFAEED353DDD778" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="type">
<paragraph id="B9A7119B4CC3D3425E92AC4D20BB89D5" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB9CBACE17945CE33E319695F6025955" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
SOMALIA, Wodderi, 
<emphasis id="0C2E81D0D7AC25BF7161BA3A47D01C23" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Hildebrandt</emphasis>
884 (holotype B†; isotype BM001050393!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1859893004F10C03C931AEA6F8F3B27E" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="description">
<paragraph id="7808ED7DF50BBE9A1DA57BDE62A29D20" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C409B1E4EE0FC29F7E4EBE18EFBA88E5" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
Perennial herb, base woody, stems erect, to 70 cm, more or less herbaceous to somewhat woody and fastiagiate, pilose below with hairs up to 3 mm long, becoming strigose upwards, glabrescent when old and woody. Leaves crowded towards the base of the stem, diminishing in size upwards, 1-4 
<normalizedToken id="B970AC4B4E26230B75D40E20559D860E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.4 cm, oblanceolate, acute, gradually narrowed into a long petiole-like base, long-pilose, often absent; stem leaves 1-2.8 
<normalizedToken id="7CB045066E44D99E950724F6361A8F88" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.2 cm, diminishing in size upwards, all linear to very narrowly linear-oblanceolate, apparently caducous. Inflorescence a large, lax terminal thyrse up to 30 cm long, formed of dichasial cymes bearing up to 3 flowers each but commonly reduced to single flowers; bracts on main axis 5-7 mm, linear; peduncles 0.6-6 cm long, becoming shorter on the secondary and tertiary flowers, often single-flowered; bracteoles 1 mm, linear; pedicels 2-4 mm long; outer sepals 2.5-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="415A8A9309C168B5A3FED693D003FD97" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 mm, ovate, acuminate, somehat scarious but with green midrib, inner sepals narrower, strigose; corolla 8-9 mm long, white, weakly lobed, midpetaline bands strigose; ovary 2 mm long, glabrous (
<emphasis id="93B01A8F227B584DE11E58DFCCCBF275" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Hildebrandt</emphasis>
884, 
<emphasis id="8751F71E8C2193C515CCD69E38A6E1F1" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Balfour et al</emphasis>
. 116 or thinly pilose (
<emphasis id="F90C9EBA09AE6F497C5184CE134403D0" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Miller et al.</emphasis>
19120); style glabrous, divided c. 2 mm above base; stigmas c. 3 mm. Capsule glabrous or with a few apical hairs; seeds glabrous to pubescent. [
<bibRefCitation id="E998468F18DEF5BD7D5B781C6333116D" author="Miller, AG" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 759" refId="B234" refString="Miller, AG, Morris, M, 2004. Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago. Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh: 1 - 759" title="Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago" year="2004">Miller and Morris 2004</bibRefCitation>
: 517; 
<bibRefCitation id="0300EAB20592E5900BC3E74EABDD90FF" author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 234]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="178138D06C5955668654B6AA195571FB" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5705CB0D7D1AF519297EA134B891F00D" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91DF890780FC7EEDE0BD28092D1F742C" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
Somalia (type only); Socotra (
<emphasis id="43C733E1C4ADCE13AFD2539897CEE083" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Balfour et al.</emphasis>
116, 
<emphasis id="CE3BF9BD2EAAD8D11C105D94ABDBD11F" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Gwynne</emphasis>
19, 
<emphasis id="3DC46C1877367DEFF65F8DD84291E0AF" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Thulin &amp; Gifri</emphasis>
8814 &amp; 8516, 
<emphasis id="31CB5BE82E03AE3CA6C1EF981778EDB9" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Miller et al.</emphasis>
10181 &amp; 19120).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02ECED7077DEFC4AA2620794B972B20E" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1000AD29B4CA05B705945F2E276CBB73" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E4D8E360D627AA463438B99018BF9B9" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
The capsule is only 2.5 mm wide, not 5 mm as described by 
<bibRefCitation id="958D823F3C73C129BBA9537DB1E8A3B9" author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44BEC9B0C81553EC346CB8C4724A29F6" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">
We agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="C8F332AD43D0042D9C57F7799E7D4ADC" author="Vierhapper, F" journalOrPublisher="Denkschrift der Kaiserlicher Akademie fuer Wissenschaft, Mathematische-Naturwissenschaft Klasse" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="321 - 490" refId="B378" refString="Vierhapper, F, 1907. Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Flora Sudarabiens und der Inseln Sokotra, Semha und Abd el Kuri. 1 Theil. Denkschrift der Kaiserlicher Akademie fuer Wissenschaft, Mathematische-Naturwissenschaft Klasse 71: 321 - 490" title="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Flora Sudarabiens und der Inseln Sokotra, Semha und Abd el Kuri. 1 Theil." volume="71" year="1907">Vierhapper (1907)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="838C3C40237C38E1FD62FDD8552321D1" author="Miller, AG" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 759" refId="B234" refString="Miller, AG, Morris, M, 2004. Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago. Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh: 1 - 759" title="Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago" year="2004">Miller and Morris (2004)</bibRefCitation>
in uniting 
<taxonomicName id="FA2EA836149D7649A91F754518272FD0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus filipes" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filipes">
<emphasis id="09937A931CEC1DBF7FC27D100324379C" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Convolvulus filipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="16F8F52381A3BBA93D346DB229CB636E" authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hildebrandtii" order="Solanales" pageId="140" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis id="E475A6EE9C7922B2BE7398FB93573E56" italics="true" pageId="140" pageNumber="141">Convolvulus hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than with 
<bibRefCitation id="F1E841E935CB0C769652D2E04F7D1D1B" author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin (2006)</bibRefCitation>
who kept the two species separate. The striking differences between specimens in stem, leaf, ovary and seed indumentum do not correlate well each other or with geographical distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
